uchs) and \"ዋ\" (her).\n- \"ጃንጂዊድን\" was split into \"ጃንጂዊድ\" (Janjaweed) and \"ን\" (object marker).\n- \"ጃንጣላው\" was split into \"ጃንጣላ\" (umbrella) and \"ው\" (the definite article).\n\n**PROTOCOL 2: THE JUDGE (Nonsense Removal)**\nNo words were discarded as gibberish or unfixable. All entries were deemed plausible Amharic words or transliterations of foreign proper nouns.\n\n**PROTOCOL 3: THE CORRECTOR (Visual Repair)**\nNo visual OCR errors or attached punctuation requiring correction were found in this batch.\n\n**PROTOCOL 4: THE LEMMATIZER (Global Citation Form)**\nFor common nouns like \"ጃንደረባ\" (eunuch) and \"ጃንጣላ\" (umbrella), the singular base form was identified as the root. For proper nouns, the word itself was generally considered the root. For suffixes/clitics like \"ና\", \"ም\", \"ኡ\", \"ን\", \"ዋ\", \"ው\", their base forms or the particle itself were used as roots.\n\n**PROTOCOL 5: THE TRANSLATOR (Nuance Expansion)**\nComprehensive English synonyms or direct transliterations were provided for each word.\n\n**PROTOCOL 6: THE GRAMMARIAN (Linguistic Tagging)**\nParts of Speech were assigned, predominantly 'Proper Noun' for foreign names/places, 'Noun' for Amharic words, and 'Conjunction', 'Suffix', or 'Definite Article' for grammatical particles.\n\n**PROTOCOL 7: THE FILTER (Size Constraint)**\nAll processed words and their split components were at least two characters long, adhering to the size constraint.\n\n**PROTOCOL 8: EXECUTIVE SUMMARY (Scholarly Guesses)**\nMany entries were identified as proper nouns based on their phonetic structure and common patterns of transliteration into Amharic from Arabic, Persian, or other languages. For instance, \"ጂያዮ\", \"ጃሃንፑር\", \"ጃሊላ\", \"ጃላል\", \"ጃሚላ\", \"ጃማት\", \"ጃባሊያ\", \"ጃቬድ\", \"ጃንቪየር\", \"ጃንጂዊድ\" are all recognized as foreign names or place names. The word \"ጃኢ\" was also treated as a proper noun, likely a transliteration of 'Jai' (a name or salutation). The importance scores were assigned based on the estimated frequency and general recognition of the words in an Amharic context.","input_words":["ጂያዮ","ጂዳህና","ጂፍ","ጃሃንፑር","ጃሊላ","ጃላል","ጃሎውን","ጃሕጃሕ","ጃሚላ","ጃሚያ","ጃማት","ጃማይ","ጃማይካዊያንም","ጃማዲ","ጃምሺዲ","ጃረር","ጃስዌል","ጃባሊያ","ጃቬር","ጃቬድ","ጃነደረባ","ጃንቪየር","ጃንደረቦቹንም","ጃንደረቦችን","ጃንደረቦችዋ","ጃንጂዊድን","ጃንጋ","ጃንጣላው","ጃኖቡለስ","ጃኢ"],"batch_number":null,"batch_label":null,"model_version":"gemini-2.5-flash"},{"id":"595cff91-1cd2-4ee4-b2fc-0dbea33cf647","created_at":"2026-03-02T20:01:49.265954+00:00","word":null,"source_file":"rare_words_25/chunk_0595.txt","batch_index":0,"words":[{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃከሊን","word":"ጃከሊን","synonyms":["Jacqueline"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃኩይን","word":"ጃኩይን","synonyms":["Jacquin"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃካ","word":"ጃካ","synonyms":["Jaca","Jaka"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ጃክፖት","word":"ጃክፖት","synonyms":["jackpot","prize","big win"],"importance":9},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃኮብስዶቲር","word":"ጃኮብስዶቲር","synonyms":["Jakobsdóttir"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃኮፓ","word":"ጃኮፓ","synonyms":["Jacopa"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃኮፖ","word":"ጃኮፖ","synonyms":["Jacopo"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃዋሂር","word":"ጃዋሂር","synonyms":["Jawahir"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃዋህራል","word":"ጃዋህራል","synonyms":["Jawaharlal"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃዋድ","word":"ጃዋድ","synonyms":["Jawad"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃዝሚ","word":"ጃዝሚ","synonyms":["Jazmi"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃየ","word":"ጃየ","synonyms":["Jaye"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃይሻንካር","word":"ጃይሻንካር","synonyms":["Jaishankar"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃይካ","word":"ጃይካ","synonyms":["JICA","Japan International Cooperation Agency"],"importance":9},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃዳላ","word":"ጃዳላ","synonyms":["Jadala"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Proper Noun","root":"ጃጊኤልካን","word":"ጃጊኤልካን","synonyms":["Jagiellonian